const co2Value = parseFloat(GreenLightSignal.co2Level.Co2LevelValue);
if (isNaN(co2Value)) {
  Lifx.color.skip('Invalid CO2 level value');
} else if (co2Value > 1000) { // Assuming high values as >1000 ppm
  Lifx.color.setColorIfOff('red');
} else if (co2Value < 500) { // Assuming low values as <500 ppm
  Lifx.color.setColorIfOff('green');
} else {
  Lifx.color.skip();
}
```
This code checks the CO2 level value and sets the lamp color accordingly: red for high levels (>1000), green for low levels (<500). If the CO2 level is not a valid number, or if it's between 500 and 1000 inclusive, no action is taken.

